page.title: 06Romiley Precinct (evening)
page.content: It's Two minutes past nine,we are standing outside Birches again. They have taken in all their display of fruit and vegetables, because they are closed for the weekend. The street lamps are on they are bright orange. There are only four people passing.There are no buses and only a few cars. It is now very dark, only the shop windows and the street lamps light the scene. We have only heard the Pelican crossing being used three times,a great contrast to this morning. The logo on Romiley Forum stands out most. It's much colder than this morning now but it has stopped raining.
